content_vision: Political entities don't want people to find their inner strength, but to be obedient workers.
text:
Intro:
when i'm by myself, my mind starts to wander,
put my heart in the hospital, thoughts i ponder,

Verse 1:
we'll be stompin' on haters like we're marching in a parade,
no werewolf gonna phase us, we'll keep on getting paid.
i need to hear those words, just tell me that you care,
don't mess with my heart, don't destroy me with a barely there.
i can't get her off my mind, she's always on my mental,
maniacs be crazy, but she's got me feeling sentimental.
she follows you home, my lady in the light,
she's the darkness in me that i can't fight.

Pre-Chorus 1:
check it out yo, watch me do my thing,
i'm ricky the rock 'n' roller, no one can bring me down, king.

Chorus 1:
episode 45, we back again tonight,
and trust me, it's gonna be an eventful fight.
ricky the rock 'n' roller got the crowd screaming for more,
turn it up some more, they'll be begging for encore.

Verse 2:
falling headfirst, feelin' so alive,
so different from the norm, don't need to strive.
rockin' my adidas, gotta keep it real,
that's my style, my authenticity, that's the deal.
don't need to understand, just feel it in your soul
it'll make you fly higher than any goal, and want me whole.
i want that real love, just like wearing timbos,
let's strip it down, keep it simple, we don't need no extras.

Chorus 2:
episode 45, we back again tonight,
and trust me, it's gonna be an eventful fight.
ricky the rock 'n' roller got the crowd screaming for more,
turn it up some more, they'll be begging for encore.

Bridge:
i had it all in my own little space, just wanted some affection,
but man, all i wanted was a lil' love, a little connection.
if you can't hang, then you better go back home,
we movin' up in life, hopin' out the vs,

Outro:
babylon's got us down, but we keep on moving on,
gotta find our way, keep searching till the pain is gone,

Instrumental:
no more hunger, no more pain, gonna make it right,
i bet you could see it in my eyes, even after i die tonight.

active_struct.name: The Dynamic Drive
attrs: includes a unique structure with a pre-chorus placed before the second verse
has a balance between repetition and variation
allows for a memorable finish with an instrumental section in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Epic Climb
attrs: provides a balance between variation and repetition
allows for the inclusion of an instrumental solo
builds up to a climax in the bridge and final chorus
ends with a clear and defined outro

struct_suggs.name: Rhythmic Journey
attrs: includes a strong and attention-grabbing intro
has a contrasting section with instrumental theme melody
allows for a strong finish with an instrumental build up to the final chorus in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Balanced Beat
attrs: keeps the song concise and to the point
allows for the story or message to be delivered effectively
includes variations between verse and pre-chorus sections

struct_suggs.name: Striking Syncopation
attrs: has a balance between repetition and variation
allows for a climax in the bridge and final chorus
includes a distinct instrumental break in the middle of the song

struct_suggs.name: The Unconventional Groove
attrs: includes a unique structure with a bridge placed before the second verse
allows for a break in the song's energy before building up to the final chorus
provides a strong finish with an instrumental section in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Rising Revolution
attrs: has a longer structure that allows for multiple verse-chorus-bridge repetitions
allows for added variation with a third chorus before the final outro
builds up to a climax in the final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Interlude
attrs: keeps the song short and concise
has a unique structure with a bridge placed after the first chorus
allows for a strong finish with an instrumental section in the outro

struct_suggs.name: Melodic Momentum
attrs: includes a distinct build-up to the second verse with a pre-chorus
allows for a climax in the bridge and final chorus
has a clear structure that is easy for listeners to follow

struct_suggs.name: The Musical Odyssey
attrs: has a strong structure with a combination of repetition and variation
allows for the inclusion of an instrumental solo
builds up to a powerful climax in the bridge and final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Drive
attrs: includes a unique structure with a pre-chorus placed before the second verse
has a balance between repetition and variation
allows for a memorable finish with an instrumental section in the outro

check out this feeling, it's pure satisfaction,
i ride that rolls, ain't no lookin' back in my action.
i can't get her off my mind, this girl's got a hold on me,
but i wouldn't have it any other way, she sets me free.

Verse 2:
ain't nothin' but a game, dealing with this pain,
but we gotta move them biscuits, gotta stay in the flame,
love is always welcome, but it's never the same.
better grab a pen and paper, take some notes,

Pre-Chorus:

Chorus:
toting up in miami, livin' it large,
you give me bad bad love and it's leaving me scarred,
but we are not just another hollywood facade.
let the music take control, let it lift you higher,

Bridge:
we the bomb and we 'bout to explode,
got rodan on your mind, we got you in that mode.
we are what we are, we keep it real, unglued
that's just how it is, we call it screwed.

Outro:
if i can't work my magic, what's the point in tryin'?
i'm taking off, now see, no denying.

Instrumental:
blow it in your face, stacking up these benjis
nothing you say can stop me, tryna get this oprah money with ease.

Intro:
all i see are dirty faces, society's disgrace,
and the matter of pain we deal with on the daily, can't erase.

Verse 1:
my woman always turns heads, she's a goddess in sight
nrb, i couldn't stand the way they viewed her life.
our sound just fits so perfect like a glove,
ain't no more stunting, we just flowing down the pipeline with love.
they all did decide, they don't wanna see us thrive,
but we showin love, sticking together like brother and sister, and that's no jive.
green was the color of the grass, when i was on top of the world
now my heart beats like a drum, feeling like hunted and no one's gonna unfurl.

Pre-Chorus 1:
look at that list of artists, they got soul and creativity,
spreading messages, making waves, it's a beautiful activity.

Chorus 1:
i'm not your average, you know i'm not regular,
i believe in all, that's my style and my flavor.
whenever i hear your sweet voice, i feel so alive,
and my girl keisha, she holds me down, makes me thrive,

Verse 2:
falling headfirst, feelin' so alive,
so different from the norm, don't need to strive.
rockin' my adidas, gotta keep it real,
that's my style, my authenticity, that's the deal.
don't need to understand, just feel it in your soul
it'll make you fly higher than any goal, and want me whole.
i want that real love, just like wearing timbos,
let's strip it down, keep it simple, we don't need no extras.

Chorus 2:
we savage, taking on this world with no fear
all i need is us, together we'll conquer, we'll persevere.
when life gets tough, sometimes you just wanna flee,
but when i come back, i'll splash like a whale in the sea,

Bridge:
if you can't handle the heat, don't come to my kitchen,
i'll leave you with salmonella, but i'm still kickin',
no tricks or magic, just raw talent and passion,
that's what keeps me going, no matter what happens.

Outro:
got a penthouse with a sick view, in the mandarin,
i'm the next big thing, she's dreamin' of diamonds, glam'n.

Instrumental:
you see us soaring over the city lights,
on by the night, we out here shining bright.

Intro:
we gon' munch on brownies, that's no fuss
got so many diamonds on my neck, it's a must

Verse 1:
gonna school you on how to be divine,
'cause we're the chosen ones, we shine so fine.
fiends run around, plus you too full of yourself,
but i won't let you bring me down to hell.
i'll bring you low from a mile high,
got a bomb chick named keisha by my side.
my trust in you is running thin
when you put that d* ck in their mouths, you know they'll do anything

Pre-Chorus 1:
green grass, red blood, same ol' story,
my heart still pounds like a marching army.

Chorus 1:
why do i gotta deal with this mess?
but it's all good, got my chain, feelin' blessed
wild cat ridin' with me, we unstoppable
ain't nothin' gonna slow us, we unstoppable.

Verse 2:
got a boatload of problems, but i ain't gon play victim,
i ain't gonna play on it like you know me, no need for revision.
bring down my fiddle, it's time to get loose,
they call it screwed up, but it's just motherfuckin' truth.
we fit together like a puzzle, so perfectly,
and off we go, my baby and me,
she just wants a piece of this love and i can see.
in the kitchen, stirrin' up a storm

Pre-Chorus 2:
my heart's been torn and i can't relax,
but i'll bring your whore back with these healing oohs and ahhs.

Chorus 2:
and even though they seen animals, they know i'm still a man,
i'm fighting with all my might, and i'm doing all i can.
i don't care what you say about me, call me a thief,
cause you niggas know i'm still gang, despite your beef.

Bridge:
we can drink whiskey and forget our troubles,
and when he comes through, we'll show the fn popo we ain't subtle.
that's the next president, he's got us in his hand,
but tonight we gonna dance, we takin' back the land,

Outro:
you can't find him, where your man be?
everybody buys, everybody lies, just be true like odb.

Instrumental:
you can save the discussion for another day
tell me where your man be, it's okay

Intro:
do you remember seeing the beatles live?
if so, do you still feel included in this vibe?

Verse 1:
all the lies they tell, got me stressed
but i ain't lettin' it get me, i'm still blessed
gems drop from my mouth, every word a diamond
oh oh no, they can't deny 'em.
said my name one time, now it's stuck in your head,
like a howling wolf, can't escape, i won't be led.
they move quicker, tryna get away from the truth
you throw em, but they can still see the lies from a mile.

Pre-Chorus 1:
feeling lit on this molly, i'll take it as it comes,
gotta get those eggs, mama needs some scrambled for brunch,

Chorus 1:
you have my word, you have my loyalty,
trust in me, i'll be your rock solid continuity.
she been playing me, like i'm some kind of game,
but i ain't lettin' her bring me down, i ain't chasin' no fame,

Verse 2:
if you're not genuine, then get out of my sight,
we're gonna dance till the morning light.
or destroy me with a barely audible whisper
who measures love in pain, only ends up a quitter.
ain't no time for drama, we go winnin',
if you ain't smoking bud, you can't come to our spirit circle for real, that's like tomorrow, or maybe that soon.
i can't keep my mind off that booty, it's a trap,
and all this lean got me moving like a sloth in a nap.

Pre-Chorus 2:
when the shots ring out, it's time to duck,
'cause we shootin' from all angles, nothin' sweet like barry manilow's love.

Chorus 2:
my mind on mars, my feet still on earth,
now i had to come through, show them what i'm worth.
i come at you from all sides, got you on the edge,
had it in my yard, now i'm setting the whole stage.

please let me in, wanna make you holler,
fuck on your mama, while i stir the crockpot, hotter and hotter.
i never needed anyone like i need you now
change your shirt, let's hit the town, we'll take the vow.

Outro:
if my song ever gets played, i'll take it as a sign,
my mind's on mars and i'm riding that rolls, feeling so fine.

i never needed anyone like i need you now
but you still got me feeling like a bearcat, how?

Intro:

Chorus 1:

but your heart is finally filled, no more broke.
i go where i skeet, leaving my mark behind,
never been a mark, i stand tall and shine.

Verse 2:
elevators take me high, you are so adored,

love is as welcome as a stranger in the streets,

and bag em up, gotta keep my cool
even though i'm getting heated, gotta play it as a rule.
now i had to come through, time to let loose,
hit the club, get sleazy, party like there's no use.

Pre-Chorus 2:
got my bags packed, i'm ready to fly,
embracing the unknown, i'm not afraid to try.

Chorus 2:
got that white powder on deck, don't play it coy,
and get rid of that old outfit, go change your clothes, boy.

but love ain't about hurting, it's not a deadly aim.

Bridge:
all the time, i'm grindin', no stop
keepin' my brother close, he's my rock
diamonds on my neck, bling bling
but my love for my fam, that's the real thing.

Outro:
i'll brush off the hurt and skip the game,
won't get trapped in their bullshit and shame.

Instrumental:
you know we got that white powder, that blow, that yayo
i been on the prowl, howling at the moon like a stray dog, hot and low.
